
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fang-bess-data-center-interconnect-01.txt'>
    <title>"BGP/MPLS IP VPN Data Center Interconnect", Luyuan Fang, Luis Contreras, daniel.voyer@bell.ca</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fang-bess-data-center-interconnect-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document discusses two categories of inter-connections of BGP/MPLS IP VPN and Data Center (DC) overlay networks. In the first category, DC overlay virtual network is built with BGP/MPLS IP VPN (IP VPN) technologies, the inter-connection of IP VPN in the DC to IP VPN in the WAN enables end-to-end IP VPN connectivity. In the second category, DC overlay network uses non IP VPN overlay technologies, the inter-connection of any overlay virtual network in the DC to IP VPN in the WAN provides end user connectivity through stitching of different overlay technologies.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-07-08T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
